Instruction for Physicians, Nurses and Midwives: Make sure that the client is not pregnant by using the questions listed in SIDE B. Completely fill out or check the required information. Refer accordingly for abnormal history/findings for further medical evaluation
IV. Risk For Violence Against Women (VAW)
III. Risks For Sexually Transmitted Infections
Does the client have any of the following?
History of stroke / heart attack / hypertension
non-traumatic hematoma / frequent bruising or gum bleeding
current or history of breast cancer / breast mass
III. Risk for Sexually Transmitted Infections
Does the client or the client partner have any of the following?
abnormal discharge from the genital area
score or ulcers in the genital area
pain or burning sensation in the genital area
history of treatment for sexually transmitted infections
partner does not approve of the visit to FP clinic
history of domestic violence or VAW
MEDICAL FINDINGS (Medical observation, complaints/complication, service rendered/procedures, laboratory examinations)
How to be Reasonably Sure a Client is Not Pregnant
1. Did you have a baby less than six (6) months ago, are you fully or nearly-fully breastfeeding, and have you had no menstrual period since then?
2. Have you abstained from sexual intercourse since your last menstrual period or delivery?
3. Have you had a baby in the last four (4) weeks?
4. Did your last menstrual period start within the past seven (7) days?
5. Have you had a miscarriage or abortion in the last seven (7) days?
6. Have you been using a reliable contraceptive method consistency and correctly?
If the client answered YES to at least one of the questions and she is free of signs or symptoms of pregnancy, provide client with desired method.
If the client answered NO to all of the questions, pregnancy cannot be ruled out. The client should await menses or use a pregnancy test.
